IBADAN – Nigerian Army has assured its readiness to collaborate with all the security agencies towards achieving peace and a secured atmosphere. General Officer Command­ing, GOC, 2 Division Nigerian Army Ibadan, Major General Gold Chibuisi stated this during 2021WestAfricasocialactivities, WASA, held at Adekunle Fajuyi Cantonment, Ojoo, Ibadan. Fake Soldier, 32 Other Suspects Paraded In Ibadan For Kidnap,… Customs Laments Loss Of 4 FOU ‘A’ Officers To Smugglers, Arrest… Major General Chibuisi said it was a common knowledge that the Nigerian Army had in recent times strived to ensure that all forms of threats to the national security were con­tained through various mech­anisms and synergy among security agencies. The GOC also stated that WASA also provides an envi­ronment for personnel and their families to celebrate as it showcases the diverse ethnic and rich cultural composition of Nigeria. Major General Chibuisi added that through these, the Nigerian Army was ready to accomplish assigned missions within a joint environment in defence of Nigeria. In his contributions, Gover­nor Seyi Makinde of Oyo State said he felicitated with 2 divi­sion, Nigerian Army, Ibadan on the occasion of the 2021 WASA celebration.